    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix incorrect documentation for DAB convolutional code initialization functions\n\n### Summary\nThe documentation comments for the DAB convolutional code initialization functions were incorrectly labeled as LTE functions, causing confusion for developers trying to understand the API. This led to unexpected behavior when trying to use the DAB-specific functions since the documentation didn't match the actual function names.\n\nThe issue was identified when a developer reported that calling `ccodedab_init_inv()` didn't behave as expected - this was because the documentation incorrectly referred to it as `ccodelte_init_inv()`.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair1/PHY/CODING/coding_defs.h`: Corrected the function documentation comments for `ccodedab_init()` and `ccodedab_init_inv()` to properly identify them as DAB functions instead of mislabeling them as LTE functions.\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Look up the documentation for `ccodedab_init()` or `ccodedab_init_inv()` in the header file\n2. Notice that the documentation incorrectly refers to them as LTE functions\n3. This causes confusion when trying to understand which function to call for DAB vs LTE encoding\n\nThe fix ensures that the documentation now correctly matches the function names and their intended purpose.\n"
}